title: Increased Eye Floaters
description: Noticed a lot more grey floaters, especially in bright light. Interferes with reading or screen work sometimes.

title: Fatigue
description: Feeling unusually tired despite sleeping enough. Noticed a lack of motivation and slow mental processing.

title: Gluten consumption
description: Ate pizza with wheat flour. Felt bloated and brain foggy a few hours later.

title: Hashimoto's flare-up?
description: Symptoms include brain fog, irritability, dry skin, and mild depression. Not sure if it's a flare-up or just hormonal.

title: Diarrhea after meal
description: Had a loose bowel movement after eating at a restaurant. Suspect oil or dairy could be a trigger.

title: Skin allergy - Itchy rash
description: Red itchy patches appeared on forearms. Possibly related to detergent or new skincare product.

title: Dry skin
description: Skin feels flaky and dry, especially around nose and cheeks. Started applying moisturizer more frequently.

title: Brain fog
description: Difficulty concentrating, memory lapses, especially in the mornings. Feels like mind is cloudy.

title: Hospital visit for eye symptoms
description: Went to the hospital due to concern about increase in eye floaters and brief flashes of light. Doctor didnâ€™t find anything urgent but recommended further follow-up.

title: Exhaustion after workout
description: Felt extremely tired after a light workout. Needed to sleep for over an hour immediately after.

title: Extreme tiredness after alcohol
description: Drank two glasses of alcohol on a night out. Felt wiped out for two days afterward. Brain fog and low energy.
